- [ ] 1. Review current solution
  - [ ] 1.1. Document proposed approach
    ```markdown
    # Current Solution
    - Core approach:
    - Implementation details:
    - Expected outcomes:
    ```
  - [ ] 1.2. List all assumptions made
  - [ ] 1.3. Identify potential gaps
  - [ ] 1.4. Note areas of uncertainty

- [ ] 2. Deep research phase
  - [ ] 2.1. Scan related files
    ```bash
    # Find all potentially related files
    find . -type f -name "*pattern*"
    ```
  - [ ] 2.2. Review documentation
  - [ ] 2.3. Search for similar patterns
  - [ ] 2.4. Document findings and insights

- [ ] 3. Challenge solution
  - [ ] 3.1. Question each component
    ```markdown
    # Component Analysis
    - Why this approach?
    - What could break?
    - What's missing?
    ```
  - [ ] 3.2. List potential issues
  - [ ] 3.3. Identify edge cases
  - [ ] 3.4. Document concerns

- [ ] 4. Iterate until certain
  - [ ] 4.1. Address each concern
  - [ ] 4.2. Research unclear areas
  - [ ] 4.3. Ask clarifying questions
  - [ ] 4.4. Repeat steps 1-3 until:
    ```markdown
    # Confidence Checklist
    - All components understood
    - Edge cases covered
    - No remaining questions
    - Implementation clear
    - Potential issues addressed
    ```
